<i>Episode 9</i>

36
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:08,910
At this stage,

37
00:02:09,350 --> 00:02:10,800
just tell me the truth, General.

38
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:14,080
Do you have it or not?

39
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:17,310
We’ve assisted His Majesty for years

40
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,550
and we know how tough the situation is.

41
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:22,360
He’s new to the throne
with little support.

42
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:23,960
If he doesn’t have the Tiger Tally,

43
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:25,800
what will he

44
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:28,960
and court officials think?

45
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,990
General, you’ve already retired

46
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:35,430
and don’t need it anymore.

47
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:38,200
Count Rong, the Tally was gone

48
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,310
when General was attacked.

49
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:43,240
Our two families
have been close for years.

50
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:45,640
I’m utterly disappointed

51
00:02:46,430 --> 00:02:48,800
that you aren’t working

52
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:52,520
to seize the assassin first.

53
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:57,240
I’ve told you everything.

54
00:02:58,110 --> 00:02:58,830
You...

55
00:03:00,110 --> 00:03:01,990
should leave.

56
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:16,480
His Majesty has sent Count Rong here.

57
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,680
Princess, the Tally...

58
00:03:20,310 --> 00:03:22,920
Yan Hui and the others must’ve
provoked His Majesty

59
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,640
into asking the Tally back.

60
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,150
Once it falls into someone else’s hand,

61
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:33,110
our family will be doomed.

62
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,430
I didn’t expect

63
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:42,960
that was the last time I saw Count Rong.

64
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:47,920
After Father passed away,

65
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,710
Mother had his death
investigated thoroughly.

66
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:53,760
Yet in a few days,

67
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,360
she hung herself in the room

68
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:59,760
following my brother’s mysterious death,

69
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:01,870
and leaving me all alone

70
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:06,110
in the palace.

71
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:09,150
I’m sorry for your family’s tragedy,

72
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:14,830
but it has nothing to do with the Bans

73
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,870
or me.

74
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,550
Your Highness,

75
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:20,990
the Tiger Tally

76
00:04:21,080 --> 00:04:22,400
led to my father’s tragic death.

77
00:04:23,790 --> 00:04:25,760
How could you deny it?

78
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:27,830
How dare you!

79
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,880
Are you accusing me

80
00:04:30,150 --> 00:04:32,640
of murdering your parents?

81
00:04:32,790 --> 00:04:33,790
I wouldn’t dare.

82
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:36,560
But the clues I’ve collected

83
00:04:37,030 --> 00:04:38,270
these years

84
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,080
all point to General Ban’s Tiger Tally.

85
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,910
Please give me an explanation.

86
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,710
That’s the least I deserve.

87
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:49,830
I said

88
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,560
the Bans have nothing to do with it.

89
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,910
Your Highness,

90
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,760
Father once said

91
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:09,400
the Bans and the Rongs
had been friends for generations.

92
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,670
Please...

93
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,320
Let me be clear.

94
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,910
Whatever you are up to

95
00:05:14,910 --> 00:05:16,000
is your business.

96
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,270
Our family won’t interfere.

97
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:23,000
Stay away from Hua,

98
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:25,350
or as the one watching you grow up,

99
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:28,470
I’m sure His Majesty would like to know

100
00:05:29,710 --> 00:05:33,790
what you’ve done behind his back.

101
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,150
I understand.

102
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:51,120
His Majesty also cares a lot about you

103
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,230
and he won’t turn a blind eye

104
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:57,080
to your disease.

105
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,030
Stop!

106
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,590
I’m already over it.

107
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,470
Be a bigger man, can’t you?

108
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:26,440
Never mind.

109
00:06:27,230 --> 00:06:28,270
It’s my fault

110
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,760
that I’m more understanding than others.

111
00:06:31,910 --> 00:06:32,760
Whatever disputes we have,

112
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,960
the birthday banquet must go on.

113
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,670
In order to work together,

114
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,270
one must compromise.

115
00:06:39,710 --> 00:06:41,000
So I’ve forgiven you

116
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,120
regarding the Longjing Cake.

117
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,440
But just so you know,

118
00:06:43,910 --> 00:06:44,960
from now on,

119
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:47,560
I’ll be in charge of everything

120
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,910
in regard to the banquet.

121
00:06:55,710 --> 00:06:56,520
Say something!

122
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:00,120
What’s there to say?

123
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,150
Why didn’t you respond

124
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:06,320
to all that I’ve said?

125
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:09,000
Aren’t you a role model for scholars?

126
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,670
Where are your manners?

127
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,910
I apologize for everything.

128
00:07:13,710 --> 00:07:14,710
Please excuse me.

129
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:16,760
Good day.

130
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:21,400
Rong Xia, what’s wrong with you?

131
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,200
What’s that attitude?

132
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:26,150
Do I owe you anything or my family does?

133
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,200
Why are you laughing?

134
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,520
I’m laughing at myself.

135
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,120
I assumed

136
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:40,120
you’d be different.

137
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,200
You’re right.

138
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:46,030
You don’t owe me anything.

139
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,710
Neither does your family.

140
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:49,470
I’m the one to blame

141
00:07:49,470 --> 00:07:50,790
from beginning to end.

142
00:07:51,350 --> 00:07:52,320
I shouldn’t have

143
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,670
dragged the Bans

144
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:56,350
or you into this.

145
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:01,230
I was alone

146
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,520
and I’ll always be.

147
00:08:03,910 --> 00:08:05,270
I’m used to it.

148
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,000
Rest assured.

149
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:10,320
I’ll never bother you again.

150
00:08:14,230 --> 00:08:15,760
What was that?

151
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,030
It’s just some dessert, isn’t it?

152
00:08:19,440 --> 00:08:20,230
What’s the matter with him?

153
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,960
What a grand banquet!

154
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:28,880
I heard Crown Prince arranged it.

155
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,000
That’s right.

156
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:33,000
No wonder it’s above the standard.

157
00:08:33,270 --> 00:08:34,270
Everyone is here.

158
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,270
I know.

159
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,600
-Prince Luo.
-Prince Luo.

160
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:40,760
Let’s go.

161
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:44,880
Cousin,

162
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:47,430
I didn’t ask you to copy sutras for me.

163
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:48,950
Whatever game you’re playing,

164
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:50,760
I haven’t forgiven you.

165
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,070
Don’t feel so good about yourself.

166
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,430
You’re in bad luck.

167
00:08:56,430 --> 00:08:57,760
I did that to help you.

168
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:01,600
I...

169
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,310
Are you alright?

170
00:09:07,334 --> 00:09:09,334
<i>Yan Zhen, Eldest Son of the Yans,
The Most Spoiled Young Master in Daye</i>

171
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,480
Your Grace,

172
00:09:13,910 --> 00:09:15,670
